Demand per region
Using the values \(L_{r,y}\) (deliveries in region \(r\) year \(y\)), we calcuate the fraction \(d_{gr}\) as follows:
\[\begin{equation}
\bar{L}_r = \frac{1}{Y} \sum_{y=1}^{Y} L_{r,y}
\end{equation}\]
\[\begin{equation}
d_{gr} = \frac{\bar{L}_r}{\sum_{r} \bar{L}_r}
\end{equation}\]
This demand is global for all patient groups. As we do not have detailed info on the demand per pation group, we multiplyby the obtained global demands by the statistics on delivery type [DREES (2021)].
